if // if GetSubsystem()-\u0026gt;GetWindow();  instead gr-\u0026gt;GetWindow(); is used, then mouse is allways visible, even if mouse is hidden with code. And I am not sure if I get really main window wtih GetSubsystem.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-12-16T10:38:24.825Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":38,"readers_count":37,"score":22.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":3851,"topic_slug":"how-to-obtain-window-from-urho-application","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":22479,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2017-12-16T17:42:45.271Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI’m pretty sure you should \u003cem\u003enot\u003c/em\u003e be doing that (creating a \u003ccode\u003enew Graphics\u003c/code\u003e) - I think doing so requests the GPU twice, and probably tries to create two windows (though I’ve not looked at the code to see). Whether or not that is okay, the \u003ccode\u003eGetSubsystem\u0026lt;Graphics\u0026gt;-\u0026gt;GetWindow()\u003c/code\u003e approach should be correct. I’m not certain what you mean by “main window” - isn’t there only one? My guess about your mouse visibility issue is that, assuming you’ve set it up correctly in Urho, Sciter probably makes the mouse visible on its end, though I can’t say for sure…\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-12-16T